UID:new-inc-year-13-mentor-open-call-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T114944Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260708
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260709
SUMMARY:Deadline: NEW INC Year 13 Mentor Open Call
DESCRIPTION:NEW INC\, the New Museum's cultural incubator\, is seeking ment
 ors for Year 13 of its program supporting creative practitioners at the in
 tersection of art\, design\, and technology. This is a call for mentors (c
 reative and business leaders)\, not for program members. TWO MENTOR TYPES:
  Dedicated Mentors ($500 honorarium) are matched one-on-one with a member 
 and commit to ongoing support throughout the year\; Office Hours Mentors (
 $300 honorarium) offer one-on-one sessions to the broader community on an 
 as-needed basis. All mentors receive a one-year All Access Plus membership
  to the New Museum\, invitations to special events including the annual DE
 MO Festival\, and access to community-only workshops\, talks\, and social 
 events. YEAR 13 PROGRAM TRACKS mentors may support: Art & Code\; Creative 
 Science\; Extended Realities\; Launchpad\; Social Architecture. KEY DATES:
  Mentor Open Call closes 8 July 2026\; Mentor Open House (virtual info ses
 sion) 17 June 2026\, 12-1pm ET (register via the site)\; mandatory Dedicat
 ed Mentor matchmaking ranking session 11 September 2026\; mandatory Dedica
 ted Mentor matchmaking event 18 September 2026\; Dedicated Mentor matches 
 announced 2 October 2026. Most NEW INC activities take place Monday-Friday
 \, 10am-6pm ET. Apply at https://www.newmuseum.org/new-inc/open-call/.\n\n
 Organisation: NEW INC (New Museum Incubator)\nLocation: New York\, NY\, US
 A\; primarily in-person at 250 Hudson St\, lower Manhattan. Some hybrid pa
 rticipation possible.\nAward: Dedicated Mentors: $500 honorarium. Office H
 ours Mentors: $300 honorarium. All mentors also receive a one-year All Acc
 ess Plus membership to the New Museum. No application fee.\nDuration: Year
  13 program (September 2026 onward)\; average 4-8 hours of engagement per 
 week.\n\nMore: https://www.newmuseum.org/new-inc/open-call/?utm_source=art
 ificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.newmuseum.org/new-inc/open-call/?utm_source=artificialnouve
 augrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:New York\, NY\, USA\; primarily in-person at 250 Hudson St\, lower
  Manhattan. Some hybrid participation possible.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ucross-general-residency-spring-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T114944Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260715
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260716
SUMMARY:Deadline: Ucross General Residency (All Disciplines): Spring 2027
DESCRIPTION:Ucross offers fully funded artist residencies on a working catt
 le ranch in the foothills of Wyoming's Bighorn Mountains\, providing unint
 errupted time and space free from the pressures and distractions of daily 
 life. Founded in 1981 with its first residency period in 1983\, Ucross hos
 ts approximately 115 individuals per year. Residencies range from two to s
 ix weeks\; at any one time up to ten people are in residence\, typically f
 our writers\, four visual artists\, and two composers. Each artist receive
 s living accommodations\, meals\, and work space at no charge. Lunches and
  dinners are prepared Monday to Friday by a professional chef (lunches del
 ivered to studios\, group dinners at 6 p.m.)\, with ample provisions for b
 reakfasts and weekends\; towels\, linens\, and weekly housekeeping are pro
 vided\, and there is cell service and wireless internet throughout. Reside
 nts provide their own working materials and arrange their own travel to Sh
 eridan\, Wyoming. The program is open to visual artists\, writers\, compos
 ers\, choreographers\, interdisciplinary artists\, performance artists\, a
 nd collaborative teams\; applicants must exhibit professional standing in 
 their field\, and both established and emerging artists are encouraged to 
 apply. Applications are submitted by discipline category: dance\, music/so
 und\, performance\, film/video\, playwriting/screenwriting\, visual art\, 
 fiction\, nonfiction\, poetry\, or interdisciplinary. The work sample and 
 project proposal are the most significant features of the application and 
 should correspond to one another\; if your work is in a single discipline\
 , select the category that best fits your project\, and apply under interd
 isciplinary only if the project genuinely combines multiple disciplines. W
 ork-sample requirements by category: DANCE\, 2-3 video files (each up to 8
  minutes and 200 MB\, or up to 3 Vimeo links\, with a timestamp if longer 
 than 8 minutes)\; MUSIC/SOUND\, 3-5 audio files (each up to 8 minutes and 
 200 MB\, or up to 3 Vimeo links\; musical scores welcome)\; PERFORMANCE an
 d FILM/VIDEO\, 1-3 video files (each up to 5 minutes and under 200 MB\, or
  up to 3 Vimeo/YouTube links\, with a timestamp if longer than 5 minutes)\
 ; PLAYWRITING/SCREENWRITING\, one complete play double-spaced noting the 2
 0-page section to read\; VISUAL ART\, 10 images at 4x6 inches and 300 dpi 
 (JPG or TIF\, no PDFs) plus a data sheet listing title\, medium\, size\, a
 nd year\; FICTION and NONFICTION\, 20 pages of double-spaced writing\; POE
 TRY\, 6-10 poems (10 maximum) in one PDF\, each poem starting on a new pag
 e\, total not exceeding 15 pages\; INTERDISCIPLINARY\, samples representin
 g the genres you plan to work in\, combining any of the above. All written
  work samples must be in English. There is a USD 40 application fee. The o
 pen call for the Spring 2027 session is open May 1 to July 15\, 2026 (appl
 y by 11:59 p.m. MT on July 15). Dedicated Fellowships for Native American 
 Visual Artists and Writers and a separate Culinary Residency are also offe
 red.\n\nOrganisation: Ucross Foundation\nLocation: Sheridan\, Wyoming\, US
 A\nAward: No charge for the residency\; living accommodations\, meals\, an
 d work space provided. USD 40 application fee.\nDuration: Spring session (
 February through early June 2027)\; residencies range from two to six week
 s\n\nMore: https://www.ucrossfoundation.org/residency-program.html?utm_sou
 rce=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.ucrossfoundation.org/residency-program.html?utm_source=arti
 ficialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Sheridan\, Wyoming\, USA
END:VEVENT
